# VibeNotch

Modular notch platform for macOS. Transforms the MacBook notch into a configurable hub powered by built-in modules.

## Architecture

```
Package.swift / project.yml → 3 targets:
  VibeNotchCore (library)       — Module protocol, registry, CommandRunner, Yabai models
  VibeNotch (executable/app)    — Shell notch/statusbar/settings + modules
  YabaiBarSignalHelper (tool)   — CLI helper for yabai signals
```

## Build Commands

```bash
swift build          # Quick compilation check
swift test           # Run unit tests
bash scripts/build-app.sh  # Full .app bundle (xcodegen → xcodebuild → dist/)
```

## Deploy & Test (CRITICAL)

After ANY code change:
```bash
pkill -9 -f "VibeNotch" 2>/dev/null; sleep 1
bash scripts/build-app.sh
rm -rf /Applications/VibeNotch.app
cp -R dist/VibeNotch.app /Applications/VibeNotch.app
open /Applications/VibeNotch.app
```

Never use `swift run` — always build and install the .app bundle.

## Swift 6.2 Conventions

- `@MainActor` on all UI classes (views, controllers, view models)
- `@Published private(set)` for observable properties
- `Sendable` on shared data types
- `@unchecked Sendable` only for AppKit wrappers (e.g., NotchSlotContent with AnyView)
- Combine: always `.receive(on: RunLoop.main)` before `.sink`
- No `import Foundation` if `import AppKit` suffices

## Naming

- Files: PascalCase (AppModel.swift, NotchSurfaceView.swift)
- Module types: `{Name}Module` prefix (YabaiModule, JiraModule)
- Core types: `Notch` or `VibeNotch` prefix (NotchSurfaceView, VibeNotchModule)
- Module IDs: `com.vibenotch.{name}`

## Philosophy

- Module-first: all user features = modules. Core only handles display, windows, orchestration
- No abstraction before 3 usages
- Spring animations only (never linear/easeIn)
- macOS native APIs (NSPanel, NSStatusItem, NSHapticFeedbackManager)
- Delete unused code, no feature flags
